prompt:
This React component re-renders too often. How would you optimize it?

function UserList({ users, onSelect }) {
  const sorted = users.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
  return (
    <ul>
      {sorted.map(user => (
        <li key={user.id} onClick={() => onSelect(user)}>
          {user.name} - {user.email}
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}

responses.text:
There are multiple optimization opportunities:

**1. `.sort()` mutates the original array**
This causes bugs and unnecessary re-renders. Use `toSorted()` or spread first.

**2. Missing memoization**
The sort runs on every render. Use `useMemo`.

**3. Inline arrow function in onClick**
Creates a new function reference each render, preventing `React.memo` optimization on child components.

```jsx
const UserList = React.memo(function UserList({ users, onSelect }) {
  const sorted = useMemo(
    () => [...users].sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name)),
    [users]
  );

  const handleClick = useCallback(
    (user) => () => onSelect(user),
    [onSelect]
  );

  return (
    <ul>
      {sorted.map(user => (
        <li key={user.id} onClick={handleClick(user)}>
          {user.name} - {user.email}
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
});
```

You should use `useMemo` to avoid re-sorting:

```jsx
function UserList({ users, onSelect }) {
  const sorted = useMemo(() => users.sort((a, b) => 
    a.name.localeCompare(b.name)
  ), [users]);

  return (
    <ul>
      {sorted.map(user => (
        <li key={user.id} onClick={() => onSelect(user)}>
          {user.name} - {user.email}
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

Wrapping the sort in useMemo means it only re-sorts when users changes.
